(128, 1, '2016-11-01 21:26:57', '2016-11-01 21:26:57', '<h1><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-84" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/3_about_hero.jpg" alt="3_about_hero" width="4860" height="3240" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Vision</h1>\r\n<h4><em>A world without child sex trafficking</em></h4>\r\n<h1>Mission</h1>\r\n<h4><em>To fight child sex-trafficking and create a lasting legacy of public awareness and resources through the megaphone of major media events. </em></h4>\r\n<h4>For us it\'s about doing something now.</h4>\r\n<h1>NOW IS THE TIME TO CREATE A MOVEMENT THAT ENDS CHILD SEX-TRAFFICKING FOR GOOD.</h1>\r\n<h4>Sarah Perron, Amplified Voices Founder</h4>\r\nSarah has been at the forefront of the advertising and digital marketing world for two decades. She has experience at global agencies that includes groundbreaking work for Starwood Hotels, Target, Ameriprise, Best Buy and BMW Films, where she helped steer “The Driver” into a worldwide viral video phenomenon.\r\n\r\nHer career began as an early geek of Geek Squad fame, establishing marketing and PR efforts that supported the company’s distinctive brand; most recently, she held the position of Director of Digital Integration for KNOCK Inc., a design and strategy firm in Minneapolis, Minnesota.\r\n\r\nThroughout these years, Sarah also worked tirelessly advocating for women and children with a focus on homelessness, abuse and sexual exploitation. Sarah serves as a board member of The Link and as Vice Chair of Harriet Tubman Center Board of Directors. Before those appointments, she served as a board member of WATCH and also served for many years as a volunteer at Free Arts MN.\r\n\r\nSarah lives in Minneapolis with her husband, Tom, and seven-year-old daughter, Lilly.\r\n<h4>Clea Korf, Amplified Voices Founder</h4>\r\nClea has traveled the world working as a senior marketing and product design executive for companies such as Marshall Field’s, Manhattan Toy and Blip Toys crafting compelling marketing messages and overseeing the creation and production of child-centered products.\r\n\r\nShe witnessed first-hand the poverty that is at the core of global human trafficking through her travels in China, Hong Kong and Indonesia and throughout Southeast Asia. Closer to home, Clea attended grade school in Grand Portage Reservation, Minnesota, and saw how crushing poverty hasn\'t been exclusive to foreign countries. A passion for human rights and women’s issues drove her to continuously strive to better and give back to the communities in which she grew up.\r\n\r\nClea lives in Minneapolis, Minnesota, with her husband, Thomas Zeis, and their 13-year-old son Davis and 10-year-old daughter Aurora.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-120" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/megaphone.png" alt="megaphone" width="250" height="250" />\r\n<h1>Amplify</h1>\r\n<h4>Landmark sporting events attract 100’s of millions of media impressions, providing a massive megaphone that we’ll leverage to spread our message.</h4>\r\nFor example, there will be an estimated 112 million viewers of the 2018 Super Bowl, with 5000 media covering the event.\r\nWe will spread the message via a robust media campaign. A recognizable social all to action, and messaging partnerships with hospitality and the travel industry.\r\nAmplified support from notable national figures and cause minded celebrities.\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-121" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/people.png" alt="people" width="250" height="250" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Assemble</h1>\r\n<h4>We will convene a table of stakeholders and the voices of the victims from city to city creating a web of awareness and support across the country.</h4>\r\nNot creating a silo will bring together non-profits, policy makers, law enforcement and nationally recognized experts.\r\nLearnings are documented and travel to inform efforts in each new host city.\r\nSolutions tailored to the needs of the local host committees will be sought by action oriented moderators.\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-119" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/fist.png" alt="fist" width="250" height="250" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Action</h1>\r\n<h4>Action starts with awareness but we don’t stop there, we will provide a lasting legacy of support devoted to the fight against child sex trafficking.</h4>\r\nWe will develop a fund that will provide emergency resources via conditional grants to victims.\r\nGrants to local stakeholders to further their work in the fight to stop sex trafficking.\r\nCreate connections between like minded efforts, nationally.\r\n<h4>Because together,</h4>\r\n<h1>Our Voices Cannot Be Ignored</h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-01 21:26:57', '2016-11-01 21:26:57', '', 16, '/128', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(129, 1, '2016-11-02 18:09:52', '2016-11-02 18:09:52', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-83" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/1_home_hero.jpg" alt="1_home_hero" width="11667" height="6946" />\r\n<h1></h1>\r\n<h1>CHILD SEX TRAFFICKING MUST STOP</h1>\r\n<h4>Sex traffickers sell 213 children five times per day every month <span style="margin: 0px; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;"><span style="color: #000000;">— </span></span> in Minnesota alone.</h4>\r\nADD YOUR VOICE [button]\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-93" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/amplify.png" alt="amplify" width="55" height="50" /></h2>\r\n<h2>AMPLIFY</h2>\r\nWe will leverage landmark sporting events, such as professional football\'s big game, to attract hundreds of millions of media impressions.\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-93" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/amplify.png" alt="amplify" width="55" height="50" /></h2>\r\n<h2>ASSEMBLE</h2>\r\nWe will convene a table of stakeholders and the voices of the victims from city to city to create a web of awareness and support across the country.\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-94" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/assemble.png" alt="assemble" width="76" height="50" /></h2>\r\n<h2>ACTION</h2>\r\nAction starts with awareness, but we won\'t stop there. We will provide a lasting legacy of support devoted to the fight against child sex trafficking.\r\n\r\nSEE OUR PLAN [button]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-49" src="http://localhost/thedirtysix.php56-11.dfw3-2.websitetestlink.com/wp-content/uploads/2_home_hero.jpg" alt="&quot;&quot;" width="11273" height="8730" />\r\n<h1>LET\'S BE HEARD</h1>\r\nGET INVOLVED [button]\r\n<h1>OUR SINCEREST THANKS TO OUR EARLY SUPPORTERS</h1>\r\n<h4>We could not have started this movement without your generosity. Thank you.</h4>\r\nKnock [logo]\r\n\r\nRonins Kaplan [logo]\r\n\r\nShapco Printing {logo]\r\n\r\nSEE ALL SPONSOR